My review is five stars only because of an outstanding employee named Ray. He went above and beyond to change my experience here. I stopped in to check out your selection of toys. The moment I walked in, I was taken back by the rudeness of another employee (I believe his name was Erik) was having with another customer. I was interested in looking at a product that was locked in a case but when I asked for help, he (Erik?) just rolled his eyes and said "ya ya". As if I was bothering him. I became extremely frustrated with his lack of customer service, and unwillingness to help me when I had only been in there for a few minutes. I was just about to leave but Ray must have noticed my irritation, and quickly approached me. Not only did he show me the product I was originally interested in but also suggested alternatives. I'm sure it's hard for females to step in to begin with, but there is no need to be blatantly disregarded like I initially was. I'll make sure to call before I come in next time just to make sure that Ray is working.

Thank you for all of your help Ray and for changing my experience!

Entered the store around 10:05, I had never been in to the specific location before so I was very excited to say the least.
I was mapping out in my head the 4 for $20 panties I would purchase, along with the $45 wig, that I had specifically come to the store to buy. Guaranteed I would have purchased more than enough to make this a $100+ trip.

Disappointed every time!! This rating is not based on the staff or specific store. I just try to shop this location first because it's in my neighborhood. Review is based on Fascinations product selection/availability.
This is the second time in a month I had to truck down to Castle because they had what I was looking for. First time was edible body lotion. It's a thing. I was told they never heard of any such product. Who wouldn't want to moisturize before going out with partner and taste yummy anywhere he puts his lips? Second time was an inflatable plug...I even looked on the website first. Thought I was good to go. I get to store...NOPE don't have it. Not only does the website NOT mention "online only" the staff at store tells me each location carries different products(and no the company doesn't give staff the tools necessary to see if a different location has it in stock). So one of the employees was nice enough to call a handful of stores to see if they may possibly carry the product. In the end it was an epic FAIL.
Fascinations
*get the web team to make product availability store specific maybe, have an online and in store option so people can better shop.
*give staff the tools to do their job
*instead of having 1 product in 8 different colors try having 4 different products in 2 different color choices. That way you have more variety in stores and better sales! I would think this would be common knowledge...

featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text:
Hi Jessica!  Truly sad to get this review from you and really want to thank you for continuing to give us the opportunity to meet your needs even though clearly, we have continued to fail here.  While we do love our friends over at the Castle, we of course want to keep you with us!  
Most important is WE HEAR YOU and we are going to work hard at getting this right!   
First, absolutely we have to identify web online specific items vs store.  This won't be quick as the amount of items/skus we offer online is vastly larger than in stores but just know it's a work in progress!
Second, I'm going crazy over this inflatable plug because we do carry in a few different vendors- so curious if it was a particular brand you were looking for that we didn't have?  We're always open to product recommendations (thank you for the edible lotion - we do carry the edible oils but will look at lotions)!  
Totally heard & totally agree on the 1 product 8 colors.  This one bit of a slow fix to work through with attrition but is currently in progress!
Last- you've brought to attention a possible training issue in stores in that we absolutely offer the capability to instantly see other stores stock so I will get with team to make sure we all understand the tools available.   And while we do carry different products in each of our stores based on consumer purchasing patterns all stores do have the same base of products, then it expands from there to meet customer need or demand and also the size/ space of a store.  
While we are disappointed in receiving this review, we totally get it.   Thank you again for taking the time out to write this review and if there are any more questions or concerns, please forward to us at info@fascinations.net.

featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Gabe, we experienced several issues with out internet provider when we opened. Connectivity dropped frequently. Sometimes it was lost in the middle of transactions. That may have contributed to this matter. The second charge that appeared on your statement was not listed as a transaction in our system. Chipped credit cards apply tokenization and encryption to guard against fraud. The second charge that appeared on your statement could not be refunded because it did not list as a completed transaction in our reporting nor to our merchant processor. Without a transaction on our end we cannot administer a refund. Refunding of this transaction had to be administered by your bank. This is a highly unusual instance and I am aware of only one other time it has happened in my six years of owning Groove. I recall fielding a question in passing roughly a month ago about a transaction that could not be found or refunded.
